 Terraform EC2 Infrastructure With Docker Installation

Project Overview

This project uses Terraform to automate the creation of AWS EC2 infrastructure.
It provisions the following:

A VPC

A public subnet

A security group allowing SSH (22) and HTTP (80)

An EC2 instance

Automatic Docker installation using user_data

Automatic run of an Nginx container on port 80

This setup demonstrates Infrastructure as Code (IaC) using Terraform.

 Architecture Components
1. VPC

CIDR Block: 10.0.0.0/16

2. Public Subnet

CIDR Block: 10.0.1.0/24

Public IP auto-assigned

3. Security Group

Allows:

Port 22 â†’ SSH access

Port 80 â†’ Web access

4. EC2 Instance

Amazon Linux 2

Type: t2.micro

Docker installed and started automatically

NGINX container runs on port 80

